<div id="community-vibe">
    <h2 class="sect-title">Community Vibe in Patterson</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Named after the Patterson family that owned a major chunk of the land in the neighborhood.</p>
            <p class="par-xl">The community in Patterson is perched atop a ridge overlooking the Edworthy Park and the Bow River valley and offers some of the most breathtaking views of the city. </p>
        <p class="par-lg">The neighborhood is also noteworthy for the Broadcast Hill Media Village that was located in Patterson Heights during the XV Olympic Winter games held in 1988.</p>
        <p class="par-lg">With the famous shopping complex the Westhills Towne Centre located at a few minutes drive down south and the Western Recreation Centre offering a variety of sports and fitness facilities, the Patterson real estate provides adequate recreational facilities to its residents.</p>
        </div>
